lign=\"center\"|32\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|4|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|5|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|1|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|4|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n|[[South Africa]]n Chart<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(B).html |title=Tragedy in South African Chart |author=John Samson |accessdate=2 June 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite book |title=Billboard 23 June 1979 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KSUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT97 |editor=Danyel Smith |publisher=[[Nielsen Business Media, Inc.]] |year=1979 |issn=0006-2510 |accessdate=7 July 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|6|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Swiss|2|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n|UK ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/1979-03-03/ |title=1979 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive - 3rd March 1979 |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |accessdate=2 June 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/spirits-having-flown-mw0000200924/awards |title=Spirits Having Flown awards on Allmusic |website=Allmusic |accessdate=2 June 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]]<ref>{{cite book|first= Joel |last= Whitburn |authorlink= Joel Whitburn |year= 1993 |title= Top Adult Contemporary: 1961\u20131993 |publisher= [[Record Research]] |page=26}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|19\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|22\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B Singles]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|44\n|-\n|US ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/70s_files/19790317.html |title=Cashbox Top 100 |date=17 March 1979 |publisher=Cashbox Archives |accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''[[Record World]]'' Singles<ref name=\"tsort\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|West Germany|2|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy|songid=561|accessdate=18 March 2019}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1979)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Rank\n|-\n|Australia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=35092 |title=Forum - 1970 (ARIA Charts: Special Occasion Charts) |website=Australian-charts.com |accessdate=2017-05-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602084720/http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=35092 |archivedate=2016-06-02}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|37\n|-\n|Canada ''RPM'' Top Singles<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.0070a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.0070a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.0070a |title= Top 200 Singles of '78 \u2013 Volume 30, No. 14, December 30 1978 |work= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |publisher= [[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate= 31 July 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|New Zealand<ref>{{cite web|title= End of Year Charts 1979 |publisher= [[Recorded Music NZ]] |accessdate= 1 May 2017 |url= http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=3868}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|15\n|-\n|South Africa <ref>{{cite web|title=Top 20 Hit Singles of 1979|url=http://www.rock.co.za/files/sahits_1979.html|accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|-\n|UK<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Top Singles 1979 |magazine=[[Music Week]] |publisher=Spotlight Publications |location=London, England |page=27 |date=22 December 1979}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|15\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>[http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1979.htm Musicoutfitters.com]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|-\n|US ''Cash Box''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/70s_files/1979YESP.html |title=Cash Box Year-End Charts: Top 100 Pop Singles, 29 December 1979 |access-date=17 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713094315/http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/70s_files/1979YESP.html |archive-date=13 July 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|19\n|}\n\n===Sales and certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|title=Tragedy|type=single|artist=Bee Gees|award=Platinum|certyear=1979|accessdate=29 March 2012|salesamount=150,000}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=France|title=Tragedy||type=single|artist=Bee Gees|award=Gold|certyear=1979|recent=false|salesamount=821,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.infodisc.fr/S_Certif_Or.php?debut=41 |title=Les Singles en Or : |publisher=Infodisc.fr |language=French |accessdate=29 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110164306/http://www.infodisc.fr/S_Certif_Or.php?debut=41 |archivedate=10 November 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>|accessdate=29 March 2012}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Tragedy|type=single|artist=Bee Gees|award=Gold|certyear=1979|accessdate=29 March 2012|salesamount=500,000}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Tragedy|type=single|artist=Bee Gees|award=Platinum|certyear=1979|accessdate=29 March 2012|salesamount=2,000,000}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| '''Total certified sales:'''\n| \n| '''3,150,000'''\n|-\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n{{col-begin|width=130%}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n==Steps version==\n{{main|Heartbeat/Tragedy}}\nIn 1998, [[Steps (group)|Steps]] covered \"Tragedy\", releasing it as a double A-side with \"Heartbeat\". It debuted at number 2 on the [[UK Singles Chart]], before climbing to the top spot in its eighth week, and achieving platinum status. It is considered their best-selling single<ref>https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/steps-biggest-selling-singles-revealed__18480/</ref> and signature song<ref>https://www.dailyedge.ie/1990s-cover-versions-786647-Feb2013/</ref><ref>https://forum.popjustice.com/threads/5-6-7-rate-the-steps-discography-rate-winner.66625/page-104</ref>.\n\nSteps's version is notable for having the dance step of putting the hands parallel to the head in time with the word \"tragedy\".<ref>https://forum.popjustice.com/threads/5-6-7-rate-the-steps-discography-rate-winner.66625/page-104</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Hot 100 number-one singles of 1979 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of million-selling singles in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 1970s]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|bee-gees|tragedy}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Bee Gees}}\n{{Bee Gees singles}}\n{{STEPS}}\n{{Celldweller}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tragedy (Song)}}\n[[Category:1979 singles]]\n[[Category:1998 singles]]\n[[Category:Bee Gees songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Celldweller songs]]\n[[Category:Disco songs]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:RSO Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Barry Gibb]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Maurice Gibb]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Robin Gibb]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Barry Gibb]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Robin Gibb]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Maurice Gibb]]\n[[Category:Steps (group) songs]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:1979 songs]]\n[[Category:RPM Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=December 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Tragedy\n| cover      = Bee-Gees-Tragedy.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Bee Gees]]\n| album      = [[Spirits Having Flown]]\n| B-side     = Until\n| released   = February 1979\n| format     = [[7\" single]], [[45rpm]]\n| recorded   = 1978\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Disco-rock]]\n| length     = 5:03\n| label      = [[RSO Records|RSO]]\n| writer     = [[Barry, Robin & Maurice Gibb]]\n| producer   = Bee Gees, [[Albhy Galuten]], Karl Richardson\n| prev_title = [[Too Much Heaven]]\n| prev_year  = 1978\n| next_title = [[Love You Inside Out]]\n| next_year  = 1979\n| misc       = {{External music video|type=single|{{YouTube|gSq_KmikENc|\"Tragedy (Live in Las Vegas, 1997 - One Night Only)\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Tragedy'''\" is a song released by the [[Bee Gees]], written by [[Barry, Robin & Maurice Gibb]], included on their 1979 album ''[[Spirits Having Flown]]''. The single reached number one in the [[UK Singles Chart|UK]] in February 1979 and repeated the feat the following month on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. In New Zealand, Tragedy succeeded the number 1 hit for 6 weeks from 18 March - 22 April.\n\n==Origin==\n[[Barry Gibb|Barry]], [[Robin Gibb|Robin]] and [[Maurice Gibb]] wrote this song and \"[[Too Much Heaven]]\" in an afternoon off from making the ''[[Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band (film)|Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band]]'' movie, in which they were starring. In the same evening, they wrote \"[[Shadow Dancing (song)|Shadow Dancing]]\", which was performed by [[Andy Gibb]] (and reached number one in the US).<ref>[http://www.songfacts.com/detail.php?id=5545 Tragedy Songfacts]</ref>\n\nThough not originally in ''[[Saturday Night Fever]]'', it has subsequently been added to the musical score of the [[West End theatre|West End]] version of the movie-[[Musical theatre|musical]]. The song knocked \"[[I Will Survive]]\" by [[Gloria Gaynor]] off the top spot in the US for two weeks before that song again returned to number one for an additional week. \"Tragedy\" was the second single out of the three released from the album to interrupt a song's stay at number one. In the US, it would become the fifth of six consecutive number-ones in a single year, tying the record with [[Bing Crosby]], [[Elvis Presley]], and [[the Beatles]] for most consecutive number-ones in the US in a single year.\n\nIn 1979, [[NBC]] aired ''[[The Bee Gees Special]]'', which showed how the sound effect for the explosion was created. Barry cupped his hands over a microphone and made an exploding sound with his mouth. Several of these sounds were then mixed together creating one large boom heard on the record.\n\n==In other media==\n\"Tragedy\" is playable as downloadable content for ''[[Rock Band 3]]'' and ''[[Rock Band 4]]''.\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n\n===Chart performance===\n====Weekly charts====\n{{col-begin|width=77%}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1979)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|2|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|3|artist=Bee Gees|song=Tragedy}}\n|-\n|[[Canadian dance chart|Canadian ''RPM'' Disco Singles]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0117&type=1&interval=50&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |title=Tragedy in Canadian Disco Singles Chart |publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate=2 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110175025/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0117&type=1&interval=50&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |archivedate=10 November 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|-\n|Canadian [[RPM (magazine)|''RPM'' Top Singles]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0134a&type=1&interval=50&PHPSESSID=